 {"id":"bd-mblr.1.3.1","title":"Critical invariant catalog for coverage accountability","description":"Define critical invariants (durability, crash recovery, MVCC conflict behavior, checkpoint correctness, schema consistency) with measurable pass signals. Output: invariant catalog with owner and test evidence hooks.","design":"Use concise invariant records (ID, statement, observable signal, priority) to avoid ambiguous prose-only definitions.","acceptance_criteria":"- Catalog names each critical invariant with failure mode, detection signal, and owning subsystem.
- Invariants cover storage correctness, MVCC semantics, crash recovery, and SQL execution integrity.
- Catalog entries include unique IDs for traceability in tests and logs.","notes":"Invariant IDs should be re-used in unit failure diagnostics and e2e event annotations.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:51.508558283Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:57:15.061792191Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T00:57:15.061773356Z","close_reason":"Created docs/critical-invariants.md cataloging 14 invariants: 7 MVCC (INV-1 through INV-7), 3 durability, 2 concurrent writer, 1 schema, 2 type system. Each has definition, owner, pass signal, and evidence hooks.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.1.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:51.508558283Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.1.3.2","title":"Invariant-to-test gap heatmap and risk ranking","description":"Crosswalk invariant catalog against current tests/coverage to identify untested or mock-only paths. Output: prioritized risk-ranked gap report feeding implementation backlog.","design":"Generate heatmap from invariant catalog plus taxonomy/coverage artifacts; avoid hand-maintained spreadsheets.","acceptance_criteria":"- Heatmap maps each invariant ID to existing tests, realism tier, and coverage signal quality.
- Risk ranking formula is explicit (severity x likelihood x detection weakness).
- Output produces implementation-ready backlog candidates with rationale.","notes":"Used as dependency input for real-backend expansion, CI gates, and no-mock unit assertion scope.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:51.764372786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:03:32.363503772Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T01:03:32.363485098Z","close_reason":"Invariant-to-test gap analysis included in docs/coverage-gap-report.md. Risk ranking: P0 (3 items - pager/mvcc/wal critical), P1 (3 items - txn/gc/schema), P2 (3 items - performance/stress). Links invariants to test evidence.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.1.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:51.764372786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.1.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:30.835108214Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
